.TH "digsig_verify" 9 "digsig_verify" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
digsig_verify \- digital signature verification with public key
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" digsig_verify
.BI "(struct key *keyring "  ","
.BI "const char *sig "  ","
.BI "int siglen "  ","
.BI "const char *data "  ","
.BI "int datalen "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "keyring" 12
keyring to search key in
.IP "sig" 12
digital signature
.IP "siglen" 12
length of the signature
.IP "data" 12
data
.IP "datalen" 12
length of the data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 on success, -EINVAL otherwise

Verifies data integrity against digital signature.
Currently only RSA is supported.
Normally hash of the content is used as a data for this function.
